{"word":"ἐρημόω","slug":"ἐρημόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐρημόω</b></el> <el>(ἐρημόω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ώσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἔρημος</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to strip bare, to desolate, lay waste</i>, <el>ἱερά</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to bereave</i> one <i>of</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἐρ. ναυβατῶν ἐρετμά</el> <i>to leave</i> the oars <i>without</i> men, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be bereft of</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to set free</i> or <i>deliver from</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to abandon, desert</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>ἐρ. Συρακούσας</el> <i>to evacuate</i> it, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>IV. </b><i>to keep in solitude, isolate</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be isolated from</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}